Use the standard library

This is how to count_distinct_characters of string:
   Remember that seen is []
   Remember that count is 0
   Remember that i is 0

   Do this string's length times:
      Remember that ch is item i in string
      When ch is more than 96, then:
         Remember that ch is diff of ch and 32
      End when
      When ch is not in seen, then:
         Add seen to ch
         Increase count
      End when
      Increase i
   End do

   The answer is count
Now you know

>>> count_distinct_characters of [120, 121, 122, 88, 89, 90]
3
>>> count_distinct_characters of [74, 101, 114, 114, 121]
4
>>> count_distinct_characters of ""
0